article.headline: IUPUI 74, IPFW 57
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- David Barlow had 23 points and seven assists to lead IUPUI past IPFW 74-57 on Saturday. Barlow shot 7-of-12 from the floor and 6-of-7 from the free throw line as the Jaguars (5-5) took advantage of 20 IPFW fouls by shooting 18-of-22 (82 percent) from the line. IUPUI never trailed and built its lead to 19 points with 30 seconds remaining. Austin Montgomery hit four 3-pointers and added 18 points for IUPUI. Quintin Carouthers scored 14 points to lead the Mastodons (3-8) in their fourth straight loss. IPFW shot just 21-of-56 (37 percent) from the floor and 3-of-17 (17 percent) from 3-point range. The Jaguars outrebounded the Mastodons 38-26 but were outscored in the paint, 26-18.
